{"id": 231333436, "title": "Faithful Tune Into Trumpet Festival", "text": "Hyderabad: The annual Hyderabad Trumpet Festival Rally took place on Saturday, drawing Christians from various denominations. The rally started at CSI Wesley Church and went to the Secunderabad station via Clock Tower before returning. Due to the pleasant weather, participants enjoyed blowing trumpets and singing hymns throughout the walk.More than three hundred people, including youth, children, and elders, joined the rally. The event's chief guest was Bishop Gollapally John of the Free Methodist Church of India.Selvin Raj, president of the Greater Hyderabad Trumpet Festival Fellowship, stated, \u201cThis festival is where we proclaim Christ's second coming. We are receiving a positive response from all denominations.\u201d", "summary": "", "url": "https://www.deccanchronicle.com/southern-states/telangana/faithful-tune-into-trumpet-festival-898015", "image": "https://www.deccanchronicle.com/h-upload/2024/06/08/1095774-screenshot2024-06-08at94808pm.webp", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 16:21:41", "author": "DC Correspondent", "authors": ["DC Correspondent"], "language": "en", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": 0.06}